            <title>[DERBY-3978] Clob.truncate(long) in the client driver doesn&apos;t update the cached Clob length</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3978</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The client driver caches the Clob length, but doesn&apos;t update it when Clob.truncate is called.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will attach a few regression tests, where one of them demonstrates the issue. The fix is also very simple; update the cached length.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
